Overall, the annual EMR for influenza A and B-associated deaths was estimated as 5.09 (95% CI: 2.20–5.09) per 100,000 individuals (

  Table 2
 ). The EMR was highest for individuals aged ≥60 years (44.63 [95% CI: 44.51–44.69] per 100,000), and second highest for children aged <5 years (2.14 [95% CI: 0.44–2.19] per 100,000). The lowest EMR was among individuals aged 10 to 19 years (0.48 [95% CI: 0.10–0.50] per 100,000). The overall annual EMR was 4.37 (95% CI: 1.49–4.37) per 100,000 for influenza A-associated deaths, and 0.73 (95% CI: –2.15–0.73) per 100,000 for influenza B-associated deaths.
